## Auto-push policy (lone-dev backup)

- This is a solo project. The user wants every commit backed up on GitHub immediately.
- After **any** commit on `main` in this repo, push it in the same step with `git push origin main`. Do not wait for the user to ask.
- Treat "commit" and "commit and push" as the same instruction in this repo.
- The only exceptions are: (a) the user explicitly says "commit only" / "don't push", or (b) the push would be destructive (force push, rewriting shared history) — in those cases stop and confirm.
- Never `git push --force` or `--force-with-lease` to `main` without explicit user request.
